1.5  Program Architecture
The 10-week programme is organised into three distinct phases:
PHASE 1 — FOUNDATIONS  (Weeks 1–4):  General curriculum for all participants. Shared frameworks, mindsets, and professional tools.
PHASE 2 — SPECIALISATION  (Weeks 5–9):  Track-based learning. Participants engage with content, guest speakers, and projects specific to their chosen pathway.
PHASE 3 — INTEGRATION  (Week 10):  Capstone week. All tracks converge for project presentations, peer celebration, and community activation.


