1.7  Program Objectives
Provide emerging professionals across sectors with clarity on career pathways and professional identity.
Equip participants with foundational and advanced skills in strategic thinking, communication, and professional development.
Connect participants with sector-specific mentors, practitioners, and thought leaders through curated guest sessions.
Foster a cross-sector community of ambitious young professionals committed to impact, collaboration, and mutual growth.
Develop participants' ability to take meaningful action through the Capstone Group Project — a real deliverable, not a classroom exercise.

1.8  Expected Outcomes
100+ participants per cohort equipped with clear career roadmaps and strengthened professional skills.
A growing multi-sector alumni network of purposeful, globally competitive professionals.
At least 3 capstone projects per cohort of sufficient quality to be shared publicly or advanced to implementation.
Continued expansion of the SLEDGE Plus advanced track and annual alumni summit.

1.9  Long-Term Vision
Over three years, SLEDGE aims to mentor 600+ emerging professionals across five sectors, building the most diverse and energised early-career network on the continent. Key milestones include:
Annual SLEDGE Summit — bringing alumni, mentors, and partners together for a flagship event.
SLEDGE Scholarship Fund — supporting 5–10 exceptional participants per cohort with learning grants.
SLEDGE Plus Expansion — a high-accountability advanced cohort (20 persons, $100/person) running in parallel.
The Ayodeji Stephen Foundation integration — aligning SLEDGE's youth development mission with the Foundation's leadership pillar.












